$interpreted: Fredrica: ...That's the condition for Atlas opening their port.
Angelia: (So that means Nigel hasn't been in Atlas all this time, and didn't want us to know about it either...)
Angelia: (...Has he gone to the East to raise an army? He can't be too pleased with the demihumans' situation...)
Dylan: Your Highness?
Angelia: ...Oh, I'm sorry. Then we shall go ahead with it.
Angelia: You've had an arduous journey, General Lucien. You should rest.
Dylan: The whole way from the desert back to Atlas is crawling with monsters. This will be an especially dangerous escort mission, we can't afford any slip-ups.
Dylan: But our forces are in short supply just now. It'll be difficult to mobilize for a while. Does Your Highness have anyone in mind for this mission?
Angelia: Hmm, let me think...
Angelia: I've got it! Captain, go find Holy Maiden Misa. She should be arriving at the Desert Kingdom soon now.
Dylan: ...I see. A suitable choice indeed. I'll look for Misa at once.
Izumi: Still waiting about?
Izumi: Yoo-hoo? Are we gonna return to the East with the door slammed in our faces, just like those Johnny-come-latelys?
Izumi: Sitting and spacing out here isn't going to get us anywhere~
Nigel: I told you, I have to get back to Atlas.
Izumi: Yawn~ Don't tell me you actually trust that sketchy fat bird?
Nigel: Got any better ideas?
Izumi: Yeah~ Let's wait until the Desert Kingdom forces come out to resupply, then whip out your blade and slaughter them. We'll rampage right into the city.
Izumi: Who cares what happens to Atlas, us two can get out and go wherever we please~
Nigel: Still cracking jokes, I see. Looks like you're in good spirits. Keep your idiotic ideas to yourself.
Izumi: Ah, I knew you'd say that... So boring. I'm serious, though~
Izumi: Ugh~ I'm telling you, think about getting your sword out and getting us somewhere~
Nigel: There's more than last time!?
Izumi: I told you, waiting around isn't gonna do us any good!
Nigel: Izumi!?
Izumi: I'm fine, but there's so many of 'em... This doesn't look too good.
Nigel: (I can see that...)
Nigel: (Damn! There's not a single break in their offence, I don't even have time to breathe...)
Nigel: (...Is this how it ends?...)
Nigel: ...I'm sorry, Eve...
Lizard General: —Eliminate the monsters!
Nigel: The Desert Kingdom Army...!?
Lizard Soldier: All monsters have been wiped out, General.
Lizard General: Hmm. They could make a counterattack at any moment. Stay frosty.
Lizard Soldier: Understood!
Izumi: What the~ The port's open all of a sudden. Found your conscience, have you?
Lizard General: This is...
Diana: Allow me to explain.
Nigel: They're saluting you, and you're wearing... You're...
Diana: Diana Juan Gomez, Queen of the Desert. We meet at last, Nigel.
Nigel: You know me?!
Diana: Holy Maiden Misa just returned with a message from Queen Angelia.
Diana: ...Atlas Deputy Leader Yamitsuki has agreed to cooperate with us, on condition that the Kingdom of the Sun negotiate with me to assist your departure.
Misa: We're grateful to Atlas for agreeing to help take the refugees. Her Highness and I are so pleased~
Izumi: Looks like we have Yamitsuki to thank for this.
Nigel: (Working with the Kingdom of the Sun...)
Izumi: I've got one question~ Who's gonna be the escort?
Ace: All hands on deck!
